','line_number':1,'multiline':True]['text':' conversion-gen is a tool for auto-generating functions that convert','line_number':17,'multiline':False]['text':' between internal and external types.  A general conversion code','line_number':18,'multiline':False]['text':' generation task involves three sets of packages: (1) a set of','line_number':19,'multiline':False]['text':' packages containing internal types, (2) a single package containing','line_number':20,'multiline':False]['text':' the external types, and (3) a single destination package (i.e.,','line_number':21,'multiline':False]['text':' where the generated conversion functions go, and where the','line_number':22,'multiline':False]['text':' developer-authored conversion functions are).  The packages','line_number':23,'multiline':False]['text':' containing the internal types play the role known as "peer','line_number':24,'multiline':False]['text':' packages" in the general code-generation framework of Kubernetes.','line_number':25,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':26,'multiline':False]['text':' For each conversion task, `conversion-gen` will generate functions','line_number':27,'multiline':False]['text':' that efficiently convert between same-name types in the two','line_number':28,'multiline':False]['text':' (internal, external) packages.  The generated functions include','line_number':29,'multiline':False]['text':' ones named','line_number':30,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':31,'multiline':False]['text':'	autoConvert_<pkg1>_<type>_To_<pkg2>_<type>','line_number':32,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':33,'multiline':False]['text':' for each such pair of types --- both with (pkg1,pkg2) =','line_number':34,'multiline':False]['text':' (internal,external) and (pkg1,pkg2) = (external,internal).  The','line_number':35,'multiline':False]['text':' generated conversion functions recurse on the structure of the data','line_number':36,'multiline':False]['text':' types.  For structs, source and destination fields are matched up','line_number':37,'multiline':False]['text':' according to name; if a source field has no corresponding','line_number':38,'multiline':False]['text':' destination or there is a fundamental mismatch in the type of the','line_number':39,'multiline':False]['text':' field then the generated autoConvert_... function has just a','line_number':40,'multiline':False]['text':' warning comment about that field.  The generated conversion','line_number':41,'multiline':False]['text':' functions use standard value assignment wherever possible.  For','line_number':42,'multiline':False]['text':' compound types, the generated conversion functions call the','line_number':43,'multiline':False]['text':' `Convert...` functions for the subsidiary types.','line_number':44,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':45,'multiline':False]['text':' For each pair of types `conversion-gen` will also generate a','line_number':46,'multiline':False]['text':' function named','line_number':47,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':48,'multiline':False]['text':'	Convert_<pkg1>_<type>_To_<pkg2>_<type>','line_number':49,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':50,'multiline':False]['text':' if both of two conditions are met: (1) the destination package does','line_number':51,'multiline':False]['text':' not contain a function of that name in a non-generated file and (2)','line_number':52,'multiline':False]['text':' the generation of the corresponding autoConvert_...  function did','line_number':53,'multiline':False]['text':' not run into trouble with a missing or fundamentally differently','line_number':54,'multiline':False]['text':' typed field.  A generated Convert_... function simply calls the','line_number':55,'multiline':False]['text':' corresponding `autoConvert...` function.  `conversion_gen` also','line_number':56,'multiline':False]['text':' generates a function that updates a given `runtime.Scheme` by','line_number':57,'multiline':False]['text':' registering all the Convert_... functions found and generated.','line_number':58,'multiline':False]['text':' Thus developers can override the generated behavior for selected','line_number':59,'multiline':False]['text':' type pairs by putting the desired Convert_... functions in','line_number':60,'multiline':False]['text':' non-generated files.  Further, developers are practically required','line_number':61,'multiline':False]['text':' to override the generated behavior when there are missing or','line_number':62,'multiline':False]['text':' fundamentally differently typed fields.','line_number':63,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':64,'multiline':False]['text':' `conversion-gen` will scan its `--input-dirs`, looking at the','line_number':65,'multiline':False]['text':' package defined in each of those directories for comment tags that','line_number':66,'multiline':False]['text':' define a conversion code generation task.  A package requests','line_number':67,'multiline':False]['text':' conversion code generation by including one or more comment in the','line_number':68,'multiline':False]['text':' package's `doc.go` file (currently anywhere in that file is','line_number':69,'multiline':False]['text':' acceptable, but the recommended location is above the `package`','line_number':70,'multiline':False]['text':' statement), of the form:','line_number':71,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':72,'multiline':False]['text':'	// +k8s:conversion-gen=<import-path-of-internal-package>','line_number':73,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':74,'multiline':False]['text':' This introduces a conversion task, for which the destination','line_number':75,'multiline':False]['text':' package is the one containing the file with the tag and the tag','line_number':76,'multiline':False]['text':' identifies a package containing internal types.  If there is also a','line_number':77,'multiline':False]['text':' tag of the form','line_number':78,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':79,'multiline':False]['text':'	// +k8s:conversion-gen-external-types=<import-path-of-external-package>','line_number':80,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':81,'multiline':False]['text':' then it identifies the package containing the external types;','line_number':82,'multiline':False]['text':' otherwise they are in the destination package.','line_number':83,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':84,'multiline':False]['text':' For each conversion code generation task, the full set of internal','line_number':85,'multiline':False]['text':' packages (AKA peer packages) consists of the ones specified in the','line_number':86,'multiline':False]['text':' `k8s:conversion-gen` tags PLUS any specified in the','line_number':87,'multiline':False]['text':' `--base-peer-dirs` and `--extra-peer-dirs` flags on the command','line_number':88,'multiline':False]['text':' line.','line_number':89,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':90,'multiline':False]['text':' When generating for a package, individual types or fields of structs may opt','line_number':91,'multiline':False]['text':' out of Conversion generation by specifying a comment on the of the form:','line_number':92,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':93,'multiline':False]['text':'	// +k8s:conversion-gen=false','line_number':94,'multiline':False]['text':' k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime contains a number of manual conversions,','line_number':117,'multiline':False]['text':' that we need to generate conversions.','line_number':118,'multiline':False]['text':' Packages being dependencies of explicitly requested packages are only','line_number':119,'multiline':False]['text':' partially scanned - only types explicitly used are being traversed.','line_number':120,'multiline':False]['text':' Not used functions or types are omitted.','line_number':121,'multiline':False]['text':' Adding this explicitly to InputDirs ensures that the package is fully','line_number':122,'multiline':False]['text':' scanned and all functions are parsed and processed.','line_number':123,'multiline':False]['text':' Run it.','line_number':130,'multiline':False]